name: Repealed
text:
REPEALED.  L 2001, c 5, §1.
Case Notes
  Payment or tender of fees and expenses of garnishee is not prerequisite to judgment against garnishee in proper case.  22 H. 723, 727.
  Counsel fees.  33 H. 337, 338; 42 H. 490.
  Costs incurred by garnishee in interpleader.  33 H. 557.
  Where garnishee has no goods or effects and owes no debt to defendant, plaintiff taxed.  39 H. 341, 345.
